            <p>The association of Crohn's disease (CD) and Sweet's syndrome is rare and 
            the presence of Sj&#xF6;gren's syndrome in Crohn's disease is even rarer, with only 
            three reports found in the literature. We describe two cases of Crohn's disease 
            associated with Sweet's syndrome, one of which is the first case of CD and 
            Sweet's concomitantly associated with Sj&#xF6;gren's syndrome. Both cases 
            responded rapidly to Infliximab therapy with complete resolution of the skin lesions.</p>
